On Escalation Ticket # 00425533 the new comment has been added: Alex Puskas:

@WaitingOnEngineer
Regarding this case, if I’m not mistaken, the customer confirmed that the solution was delivered and that the latest build is working as expected.

Can you confirm if the latest agent is working as expected?


What was fixed/observed?
For device control, the EPP agent tracks more GUIDs, services, device classes, etc. With all these information information and others, the agent can categorize devices into different types.

It seems that starting with a certain Windows version, the ADB interface classes were changed, causing Windows to detect the device differently. After investigating the issue, we found that Windows detected the device as a custom class.
After executing some ADB commands in CMD (or push Android application to phone), an additional interface was detected ( as you mentioned, everything worked UNTIL the commands were executed in CMD).
